Was curious to compare Musc Ravageur with Meharees, Labdanum 18 and L de Lolita, so did a side-by-side comparison of all four of them today. They all start like pretty much different perfumes, later in the drydown one can spot some similarities with MR.

Meharees - initially heavier on the citruses and lighter on the spices, a softer and "thinner" scent with moderate projection, yet good longevity, the drydown is closest to MR;

Labdanum 18 playing the odd one out in the beginning, obviously with more detectable labdanum, resembling more Shalimar than MR at that stage, not spicy, least sweet from the bunch, soft projection, good longevity;

L de Lolita showcasing lots of gorgeous vanilla, vanilla and more vanilla, the sweetness is balanced well though, amazing projection, good longevity, the drydown resembles MR+vanilla;

Initially Musc Ravageur is undoubtedly the winner, being deeper, more complex, richer in spices (more cinnamon than cloves), projects as well as L de Lolita.

However, after around 7-8 hours the differences between them are not that obvious. Still my favourites are MR because of how intoxicating it smells in the beginning and L de Lolita because of that yummy vanilla top note and amazing projection.

If I had to keep just one, having all four, I'd choose MR. If I didn't have any of the four and had to buy one, I'd buy MR if money allowed or Meharees if I were money conscious.
